tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: All measured parameters are within or close to normal limits, except for a mildly elevated chloride and slightly decreased total CO₂, which may suggest a mild non-anion gap metabolic acidosis. Renal function, glucose, and electrolytes are otherwise unremarkable. No acute laboratory concerns; clinical correlation is recommended.
